			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Clerics???<a name="28488"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 17 04 8:46 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>There are very active conversations on the shammy, wizzy, and of course cleric boards(haven't checked druid's), about druid/shammy heals in relation to cleric. Arguments that i see for clerics to remain the undisputed champs of healing:
<br />
1. Little to no soloability
<br />
2. No movement increasing buff
<br />
3. No invis
<br />
4. Offers almost nothing else in groups and raids other than hp buffs, rez, and heal, including insanely low dps.
<br />

<br />
Arguments that i see for druids and shammies to draw closer to clerics in terms of healing:
<br />
1. Both classes, druids more can be soloed
<br />
2. High dps
<br />
3. Brings many things to a grouping situation including slow and DS respectively
<br />
4. In most cases druids and shammies are very undesirable in grouping situations
<br />

<br />
Maybe these are all way off but i tried posting on the cleric's forum and got eatten alive. I just wanted to discuse and argue (friendly) in a nice, safe environment<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
I suggest reading some of the threads on the wizzy, shammy, and clerics boards cause they are very interesting and both sides have some very good points. I myself am in support of druids/shammies drawing to withing 75%-80% of clerics. Maybe they'd even get a full cheal like clerics, only it'd cost double the mana and double the casting time. /shrug.
<br />

<br />
Your thoughts on it all.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
