				<td colspan="2"><span>Shaman are pretty overrated.  Their slow is not materially better than chanter or beastlord slows (especially with mitigation), heals are bordering on hybrid quality (paladins were disturbingly close in healing ability, the lastest changes help though), DPS ranks behind almost any class (including clerics), and other priests perform CC as well or better.  There's basically no reason to add a shaman to most groups if there is a chanter or BST available.  I only pull my shaman out anymore if there is no other healer available... and a weak healer he is.  If the first slow is resisted a shaman can find himself in the dreaded &quot;Tnarg chain&quot;... you can do nothing but keep spamming your weak blast heal, can't even get time to attempt another slow or to canni.  That means the &quot;superior mana regen&quot; that shamans are touted for and has become a necessity to fuel some highly inefficient spells is not available.
<br />

<br />
Now, I'm not trying to say shamans suck, they are still a decent class.  But they are very, VERY replaceable.  ENC and BST slow as well as is needed for 99% of situations, and bring more to the table in other departments.</span></td>
