			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have a Druid main, a Shaman and Cleric alt, when I’m playing my Druid or Shaman I don’t care to be a healer. I'm much more affective using the spells designed for my Druid and Shaman to be concerned about healing a group. 
<br />

<br />
Perhaps its just my personal opinion but it’s a minority of Druid or Shamans that seem to be vocal about wanting to be a healer, my question to them is always why? I’m glad I can heal, I’m glad Druids and Shamans have nice heal spells but I don’t see why when you have so many other capabilities as a Druid or Shaman you want to take on the role of healer. That’s just my opinion. 
<br />
