				<td colspan="2"><span>I will take a shaman over a druid every time.  I will take a shaman over most enchanters.
<br />

<br />
As stated already, most druids are soloists and don't have good grouping skills.
<br />

<br />
Chanter haste is nice, but with bard haste, item haste and shammy haste, you can get pretty high up there anyway.  They can nuke, but guess what, they are too busy doing CC to matter most times.  They have a pet that is basically worthless, it only attacks when the chanter is attacked, totally uncontrollable, with the exception of charmed pets.  They can give you mind candy.  Well, most people these days buy it in PoK prior to going to adventure.  I've had plenty of groups where once formed and had the adventure, temporarily unformed to allow casters to go get KEI, then returned and in we went.
<br />

<br />
Shaman has over all the best buffs hands down.  No other class has as many buffs.  HP, DEX, STR, CHA, AGI, STA, Haste.  No other class slows as well per level.  They also have good pets, better than good when they buff em up.  They are not reliant on KEI or VoQ, they can canni and self heal.  A good shaman is quite perferable, IMO.
<br />

<br />
Oh, don't forget there are a LOT of poor excuses for enchanters, and a poor enchanter is a death bringer waiting to happen.
<br />

<br />
Turgur's Insects: lvl 51 shammy slow, ranges from 66% to 75% slow.  That means mobs are slowed by 2/3 to 3/4 their normal attack speeds.  So, a mob delay of 32 becomes 53.12 at low end or 56 at high end.  2/3rds possible damage mitigated to 75% possible damage mitigated.
<br />

<br />
Put into pure damage numbers, if we allow that the mob hits no matter what for 1000hp damage each landed swing with a delay of 32 and hits each swing (far fetched but let's go with it) then a battle lasting 32 seconds (all this is highly arbitrary) means that the mob would have hit a total of 10 times doing 10000damage.  Using just the low end of the Turgur's insects that damage is reduced automatically from 10000 to 3333damage.  High end it would be reduced to 2500 damage.
<br />

<br />
Would someone care to refute my observation on slow delay effects as shown above?</span></td>
