				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Clerics???<a name="28732"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 18 04 4:01 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Quote:
<br />
In most cases druids and shammies are very undesirable in grouping situations 
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Typo? I assume so because the bullet point right above this is &quot;bring lots of things to groups.&quot; 
<br />

<br />
If not a typo then a pretty controversial assertion</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
It's a paradox. Druids and shammies bring a lot to groups, but are often not desired because of their healing abilities. Many people don't play with pickup groups but at such a low lvl i have to. Haven't you ever sent a tell to someone and they respond, &quot;Do you have a cleric?&quot; sometimes i respond, &quot;well we've got 2 spots open not including yours so if one goes lfg we'll get him, if not though we have a druid who can heal&quot; usually they laugh and tell me to respond if they find a cleric. So to repeat, it's a paradox.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">"I pull what I see."
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=920626&resize=true newwindow>Inspect Me</a></span></td>
